<div class="a2">To: <b>djf</b></div>
<div class="b2">
    <p>Their duty is to ENFORCE the law. If in doing that they provide some sort of protection, that&#8217;s a bonus! The 1981 &#8216;Warren vs DC&#8217; court decision established that police have a duty to provide &#8216;protection&#8217; to the collective community but are under NO legal obligation to provide protection to individual &#8216;free&#8217; citizens. I believe that is why there has been no successful legal action brought by a &#8216;free&#8217; citizen against a policemen, a police department, a city, a county, a state, or any government agency on the basis of &#8216;Failure to Protect&#8217;.</p>

