<div class="a2">To: <b>AEMILIUS PAULUS; All</b></div>
<div class="b2">
    <p>&#8220;This is why I laugh at those supposed &#8220;rugged individualists&#8221; on this site. The rationale for these cases rises from the individualism forming one of the premises of the Common Law.&#8221;</p>
<p>I think it is much simpler. If the court ruled that the police had a duty to protect individuals, they could be sued for every crime that occurs. It would rapidly bankrupt the State.</p>
<p>I do not know of any government anywhere that allows police to be sued because an individual was the victim of a crime, unless the police had a &#8220;special duty&#8221; such as being assigned to guard someone, and then egregiously failed in that &#8220;special duty&#8221;.</p>

